OL,6,FThe long-awaited report released on
OL,7,FMonday revealed the risks were "well-
OL,8,Fknown" decades before the infected
OL,9,Fblood products were used on patients
OL,10,Fin the UK.
OL,12,FReport author Sir Brian Langstaff
OL,13,Fconcluded "the chief responsibility
OL,14,Ffor the failings lied with successive
OL,15,Fgovernments", and that they "showed
OL,16,Flittle interest in finding the truth".
OL,18,FBob is calling for a full recognition
OL,19,Fof the scandal and compensation.
